<DocsLayout title="Session Metrics" description="Track token savings and costs with ctx_metrics.">
  <p>
    lean-ctx tracks token savings in real-time during each session. Use <code>ctx_metrics</code>
    to see a comprehensive report of your savings.
  </p>

  <h2>Using ctx_metrics</h2>
  <p>Call <code>ctx_metrics</code> at any point during a session to see current savings:</p>

  <pre><code>ctx_metrics

lean-ctx session metrics
══════════════════════════════════════════════════
Files tracked: 12 | Reads: 34 | Cache hits: 22 (65%)
Input tokens:  28.5K original → 4.1K sent | 24.3K saved (85.5%)
Cost estimate: $0.4270 without → $0.0620 with lean-ctx | $0.3650 saved

By Tool:
Tool           Calls  Original     Saved   Avg%
──────────────────────────────────────────────────
ctx_read          18     22.4K    19.2K    91%
ctx_shell          8      4.8K     3.1K    74%
ctx_tree           4      1.8K     1.2K    40%

By Mode:
Mode           Calls     Saved
──────────────────────────────
map                6    12.1K
signatures         4     5.2K
full               8     1.9K

File Refs:
  F1=auth.ts [123L 915t reads:5]
  F2=db.ts [89L 412t reads:3]
  F3=routes.ts [234L 1856t reads:2]

Projected session savings (incl. thinking): $0.512</code></pre>

  <h2>What's Tracked</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Files tracked:</strong> Number of unique files cached in the session</li>
    <li><strong>Cache hits:</strong> Times a file was re-read from cache instead of disk</li>
    <li><strong>Input tokens:</strong> Original vs. sent token counts (tiktoken-exact, o200k_base)</li>
    <li><strong>Cost estimate:</strong> USD cost based on current API pricing ($15/M input tokens)</li>
    <li><strong>By Tool:</strong> Calls, original tokens, saved tokens, and average savings per tool</li>
    <li><strong>By Mode:</strong> How many calls used each ctx_read mode and how much each saved</li>
    <li><strong>File Refs:</strong> All tracked files with their reference IDs, sizes, and read counts</li>
    <li><strong>Projected savings:</strong> Estimated total session savings including thinking token impact</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Token Counting</h2>
  <p>
    lean-ctx uses <code>tiktoken-rs</code> with the <code>o200k_base</code> encoding (same as GPT-4o,
    Claude, and other modern models) for exact token counting. No estimation, no heuristics.
  </p>

  <h2>Using ctx_benchmark</h2>
  <p>
    To find the optimal compression mode for a specific file, use <code>ctx_benchmark</code>:
  </p>
  <pre><code>ctx_benchmark auth.ts

Benchmark: auth.ts (123L)

Strategy             Tokens  Savings
──────────────────────────────────────
raw                     915  —
aggressive              782  -133 (15%)
signatures              121  -794 (87%)
entropy                 198  -717 (78%)
cache hit                13  -902 (99%)
──────────────────────────────────────
Best: cache hit (99% savings)</code></pre>
</DocsLayout>
